OL,3,CThames Water boss defends #195K bonus
OL,4,Cdespite company's 'excessive' debt
OL,6,FWhen asked by MPs if it was wise to
OL,7,Faccept such a large bonus so soon into
OL,8,Fthe job at the struggling water
OL,9,Fcompany, Mr Weston said: "I think in
OL,10,Fthe first three months I did make a
OL,11,Fdifference.
OL,13,F"I started to put in place the new
OL,14,Forganisational structure, I started to
OL,15,Fgive people confidence and reassurance
OL,16,Fabout how proud they could be of the
OL,17,Fjob they did and what we were setting
OL,18,Fout to do.
OL,20,F"And that helped stabilise the company
OL,21,Fand I think that was important."
